# Architecture

## Intent

This project uses a documentation-first repository structure intended for mall-domain platform work.

## Documentation Layers

- `README.md`: entrypoint for humans and models
- `AGENTS.md`: shared collaboration rules
- `CLAUDE.md`: host-specific notes for Claude Code
- `docs/domain-overview.md`: shared domain language
- `docs/document-map.md`: explanation of document responsibilities
- `docs/roadmap.md`: staged evolution
- `docs/constraints.md`: explicit boundaries

## Design Notes

- The repository should explain itself before asking a model to infer intent from code.
- Domain language should be generic enough to stay publishable.
- Document responsibilities should be explicit to reduce overlap and drift.
- This blueprint does not imply any specific code architecture.

## Structure Guidance

- If this is a new project, a recommended application layout such as `internal/app` may be documented here.
- If this is an existing project, describe the structure that already exists before proposing any change.
